# Module Contracts

Public exports from `src/index.ts`:
- `default Sudoku` object with: `solve`, `nextMove`, `validate`, `describe`
- Named: `SudokuSolver` class
- Types: `Board`, `Move`, `PlacementMove`, `EliminationMove`, `ValidationReason`, `ValidationResult`, `SolveResult`, `MoveResult`, `MoveStatus`, `DescribeResult` (shape sources: `boardGeo.ts` / `move.ts` / `validate.ts` / `index.ts` interfaces)

Board input contract:
- Board string must be exactly 81 characters.
- Allowed board string characters: `0-9` and `.`.
- `Board` matrix input must be `9x9` with integer cell values in `0..9`.

Output contract:
- `solve()` returns `SolveResult`:
 - `isValid: boolean`
 - `board: number[][]`
- `nextMove()` returns `MoveResult`:
 - `status: "Complete" | "In progress" | "Invalid"`
 - `move: PlacementMove | EliminationMove | null`
 - `message: string` (when `move` non-null, equals `move.message`; invalid/complete use solver-generated status text)
- `validate()` returns `ValidationResult`:
 - `isValid: boolean`
 - `message: string`
 - `reasons: ValidationReason[]`
- `describe()` returns `DescribeResult`:
 - `isValid: boolean`
 - `isComplete: boolean`
 - `message: string`
 - `difficulty: "Easy" | "Medium" | "Hard" | "Diabolical" | "Impossible" | null` (`null` when `isValid === false`)
 - `solutions: number`

Move type contract:
- `Move = PlacementMove | EliminationMove` (discriminated union on `type` field)
- `PlacementMove`: `{ type: "placement"; row; col; value; algorithm; message; reasoning }`
- `EliminationMove`: `{ type: "elimination"; eliminations: Array<{ row; col; value }>; algorithm; message; reasoning }`
- Always narrow on `move.type` before accessing placement-specific fields.
- `Algorithm = "Last Digit" | "Full House" | "Naked Single" | "Hidden Single" | "Pointing Pair" | "Pointing Triple" | "Box/Line Reduction" | "X-Wing" | "Swordfish" | "Naked Pair" | "Naked Triple" | "Naked Quad" | "Hidden Pair" | "Hidden Triple" | "Hidden Quad"` (specific technique on the move; phase order in `sudokuSolver.ts` `SEARCH_PHASES`, not exported; pointing label follows box-line candidate count 2 vs 3)

Validation reason taxonomy:
- `duplicate_in_row`
- `duplicate_in_column`
- `duplicate_in_box`
- `invalid_value`
- `invalid_board_length`
- `invalid_board_characters`
- `empty_cell_no_candidates`
- `too_many_empty_cells`

Stability rules:
- Treat exported function signatures and reason type names as semver-sensitive.
- Prefer adding new fields over changing/removing existing fields.
